[{"id":"VR846554","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram with a battery, three light bulbs, and open switch. The circuit has four horizontal branches and two vertical branches. The top horizontal branch has the battery. The bottom horizontal branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 3. The inner horizontal branch immediately below the top horizontal branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 2. The inner horizontal branch immediately above the bottom horizontal branch has the open switch. The left vertical branch has a light bulb labeled Bulb 1 between the two inner horizontal branches.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR846554.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A battery, three light bulbs, and a switch are connected in a circuit as shown in the figure. With the switch in the open position, which of the following correctly states if there is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> and provides a correct justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR846554_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because charge from the battery is repelled and moves as far from the battery as possible, through Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is a current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is part of a closed circuit loop that includes a battery.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because charge from the battery will reach the open switch first and will not be able to continue moving to Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no current in Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> because the switch results in an open circuit, preventing current occurring anywhere in the circuit.</p>"],"answer":1}]